text:
The biggest buyers of Bitcoin during this price dip haven’t been retail investors—it’s been institutions, with ETF inflows running unusually high. 

But institutions are buying to HODL the asset—they’re not regularly transacting on-chain.

@MARA CEO, @fgthiel's view is that “anything we can do to drive more adoption of using Bitcoin actively… is better for Bitcoin than it just being locked up and put on a shelf.”
